
  "DIFFERENCE BETWEEN WINDOW , SCREEN , DOCUMENT IN JAVASCRIPT"
  
WINDOW 
  
   It is a global object which has number of properties and it is the first thing that is loaded in the browser while browsing.
  
SCREEN 

   It is present inside the window object and can be accessed with only its name (ie screen) since window is a global object.
   It contains some information regarding screen dimensions on which the browser displays the rendered contents.
   
DOCUMENT

   Its also present in the window object and has information of contents that are rendered and displayed (ie DOM tree)